    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: texto
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1338755759}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: control
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1089813532}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: cualNpc
      value: profe
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: jugador
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1066356808}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: puntaYclick
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1066356812}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: panelDialogo
      value: 
      objectReference: {fileID: 1201227029}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.size
      value: 29
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[0]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Oh, Hola! Que haces aqui?"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[1]
      value: (English) Oh, Hello! What are you doing here?
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[2]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Hablaste con alguien? Pero si no hay nadie aqui! Bueno,
        no importa"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[3]
      value: (English) Did you talk to anyone? But there is no one here! Well it
        doesn't matter
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[4]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Para ir al final del calabozo que es donde se encuentra
        la salida, debes aprender ingles!"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[5]
      value: (English)To go to the end of the dungeon, which is where the exit is,
        you must learn English!
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[6]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Voy a guiarte en lo que pueda, para ver si salimos ambos
        de aca, vale?"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[7]
      value: (English) I'm going to guide you as much as I can, to see if we can
        both get out of here, okay?
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[8]
      value: '*'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[9]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Primero, voy a ense\xF1arte los verbos"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[10]
      value: (English) First, I'm going teach you the verbs
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[11]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Los verbos son palabras de acci\xF3n. Se utilizan para
        describir una acci\xF3n, estado u ocurrencia. Por ejemplo, cuando alguien
        dice, (\u201CI am running\u201D), la palabra (\u201Crunning\u201D) es un
        verbo. Los verbos son esenciales para construir oraciones y comunicarse eficazmente."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[12]
      value: "(English) Verbs are action words. They are used to describe an action,
        state or occurrence. For example, when someone says, (\u201CI am running\u201D),
        the word (\u201Crunning\u201D) is a verb. Verbs are essential to construct
        sentences and communicate effectively."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[13]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) En ingl\xE9s, los verbos se dividen en dos categor\xEDas:
        verbos regulares e irregulares. Los verbos regulares siguen un patr\xF3n
        establecido. Por ejemplo, el verbo (\u201Crun\u201D) se conjugabaconjugar\xEDa
        como (\u201Crun - ran - run\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[14]
      value: "(English) In English, verbs are divided into two categories: regular
        and irregular verbs. Regular verbs follow a set pattern. For example, the
        verb (\u201Crun\u201D) was conjugated as (\u201Crun - ran - run\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[15]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Los verbos irregulares no siguen un patr\xF3n f\xE1cil
        y deben memorizarmemorizarse. Por ejemplo, el verbo (\u201Cgo\u201D) se conjugaba
        como (\u201Cgo - went - gone\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[16]
      value: "(English) Irregular verbs do not follow an easy pattern and must be
        memorized. For example, the verb (\u201Cgo\u201D) was conjugated as (\u201Cgo
        - went - gone\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[17]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Es importante tener en cuenta que los verbos tambi\xE9n
        pueden usarse como adjetivos, sustantivo y adverbios. Por ejemplo, el verbo
        (\u201Crun\u201D) puede usarse como adjetivo (\u201Ca running child\u201D),
        sustantivo (\u201Ca run\u201D) y adverbio (\u201Che ran quickly\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[18]
      value: "(English) It is important to note that verbs can also be used as adjectives,
        nouns, and adverbs. For example, the verb (\u201Crun\u201D) can be used as
        an adjective (\u201Ca running child\u201D), a noun (\u201Ca run\u201D), and
        an adverb (\u201Che ran quickly\u201D)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[19]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Hay diferentes tipos de verbos en ingles\n\nTres para
        ser exactos: (verbos de acci\xF3n, verbos de enlace y verbos auxiliares)."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[20]
      value: '(English) There are different types of verbs in English



        Three
        to be exact: (action verbs, linking verbs and auxiliary verbs).'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[21]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Verbos de acci\xF3n:\r\nLos verbos de acci\xF3n describen
        una acci\xF3n. Por ejemplo, (\u201Crun\u201D), (\u201Cjump\u201D) y (\u201Cswim\u201D)
        son todos verbos de acci\xF3n. Los verbos de acci\xF3n pueden ser regulares
        o irregulares."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[22]
      value: "(English) Action verbs:\r\nAction verbs describe an action. For example,
        (\u201Crun), (\u201Cjump\"), and (\u201Cswim\u201D) are all action verbs.
        Action verbs can be regular or irregular."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[23]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Verbos de enlace:\r\nLos verbos de enlace describen un
        estado o condici\xF3n. Por ejemplo, (\u201Cbe\u201D), (\u201Cbecome\u201D)
        y (\u201Cseem\u201D) son todos verbos de enlace. Los verbos de enlace siempre
        son regulares."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[24]
      value: "(English) Linking verbs:\r\nLinking verbs describe a state or condition.
        For example, (\u201Cbe\u201D), (\u201Cbecome\u201D), and (\u201Cseem\u201D)
        are all linking verbs. Linking verbs are always regular."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[25]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Verbos auxiliares:\r\nLos verbos auxiliares se utilizan
        para formar tiempos y expresar modalidad. Por ejemplo, (\u201Ccan\u201D),
        (\u201Ccould\u201D) y (\u201Cwould\u201D) son todos verbos auxiliares. Los
        verbos auxiliares siempre son regulares."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[26]
      value: "(English) Auxiliary verbs:\r\nAuxiliary verbs are used to form tenses
        and express modality. For example, (\u201Ccan\u201D), (\u201Ccould\u201D)
        and (\u201Cwould\u201D) are all auxiliary verbs. Auxiliary verbs are always
        regular."
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[27]
      value: "(Espa\xF1ol) Espero que con eso pueda ayudarte, nos vemos luego"
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[28]
      value: (English) I hope that can help you, see you later
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    - target: {fileID: 9045685865205016042, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
      propertyPath: lineasDialogo.Array.data[29]
      value: '(English) Different types of verbs



        There are three types
        of verbs in English: (action verbs, linking verbs and auxiliary verbs.)'
      objectReference: {fileID: 0}
    m_RemovedComponents:
    - {fileID: 3833820202715068307, guid: 84f50d681e7fa3c40bfa60642ab6991d, type: 3}
    m_RemovedGameObjects: []
    m_AddedGameObjects: []
